title.narrative: Education ministries have reliable data management, credible accountability structures and quality assurance mechanisms in place and domestic financing for education is increased by 5 per cent.

description.narrative: The 2017/18 EMIS Statistical Abstracts were finalized for Puntland State and Somaliland and have informed Joint Education Sector Reviews and sector planning exercises. In the Federal Government, delays were experienced in publishing the 2017/2018 EMIS report. A total of 11,907 Grade 8 students (39% female) sat for end of primary (Grade 8) examinations with UNICEF support. UNICEF is re-asserting our leadership role in the overall education sector dialogue, including in Early Childhood Education, and improve data quality and analysis through the Education Sector Assessment in 2020. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
